const is used to specify variable value will not be changed.
const double e=2.718819;
const char msg[]= "warning"; //elements in array will not be altered.
int strlen(const char[]); indicate that the function doesnt change that array.

系统定义的strlen(s) function returns the length of its character.

在系统里，每个string最后都包含一个'\0'
int strlen(char s[])
{
	int i;
	i=0;
	while (s[i] != '\0')
		++i;
	return i;
}

A program begins executing main priot to others. 

#include <stdio.h> include information about standard library.
(printf就是a library fuction)

Format: 打印输出格式：
%d 指明integer格式    Each % construction in the first argument of printf is
paired with the corresponding second argument,third,...Match up properly by number and type.
例子：printf("%3d %6d\n", fahr, celsius);  print first nmber each line in a field 3 digits wide
second in a field 6 digits wide.

经典考题：
I hand you a thousand $1 bills and ten envelopes. Your job is to find a way to put various numbers 
of dollar bills in those ten envelopes so that no matter what amount of money I ask you for (between $1-1000),
 you can simply hand me some combination of envelopes and always be assured of giving me the correct amount of cash.

Env #01: 0000000001(2) = $1(10)
Env #02: 0000000010(2) = $2(10)
Env #03: 0000000100(2) = $4(10)
Env #04: 0000001000(2) = $8(10)
Env #05: 0000010000(2) = $16(10)
Env #06: 0000100000(2) = $32(10)
Env #07: 0001000000(2) = $64(10)
Env #08: 0010000000(2) = $128(10)
Env #09: 0100000000(2) = $256(10)
Env #10: 1000000000(2) = $512(10)

因为binary组合可以排序成任何10进制数字between 1----1024. 所以如果需要第几位的binary digit,就把那个钱包带上。 
also，因为只负责分1000元，然而binary covers 0----1024,所以需要减去24. 所以第十个bag里的钱等于512-24=488.
在1---488内，第十个包给个0块就好了，超过才需要用到第十个包。

